# Direct (top-level) runtime dependencies for the `ecs-deploy` package.
# Mirror of `install_requires` in setup.py.
#
# The fully-pinned, hashed lockfile is `requirements.txt`, generated by:
#
#   CUTOFF="$(date -v-7d +%Y-%m-%d)"   # macOS
#   # CUTOFF="$(date -d '7 days ago' +%Y-%m-%d)"   # Linux
#   uv pip compile requirements.in \
#     --python-version 3.13 \
#     --generate-hashes \
#     --exclude-newer "$CUTOFF" \
#     --output-file requirements.txt
#
# The cooldown (`--exclude-newer`) is a 7-day supply-chain delay: we don't
# pull a brand-new package release until it has been in the wild for at
# least a week. CVE-driven exceptions are documented as
# `--exclude-newer-package <name>=<today>` overrides — see the gfi-mcp
# pattern.

